ExecDesc.value: Oracle Outside In JPEG 2000 COD and COC Parameter Heap Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A heap buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Oracle Outside In, a set of libraries used to decode many file formats. The vulnerability is exposed when the product is used to handle JPEG 2000 files. Oracle Outside In is embedded in many enterprise applications. This vulnerability can be exploited by causing an application that uses the vulnerable library to handle a malformed JPEG 2000 file. Depending on the application, user interaction may be required. Successful exploitation can result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the affected application.
